The fluorescence spectra of the same concentration of CDs-ABT solution in the presence of different concentrations of BRH are shown in Fig. 6
                        A. As the BRH concentration gradually increases from 0 to 130 μM, the fluorescence of CDs-ABT excited at 330 nm is gradually quenched. Excellent linear relationship between F0–F and BRH concentration from 10 to 130 μM is observed (Fig. 6B). The equation can be described as F0–F = 8.6791C + 160.2474, and R2 is 0.9908. Based on LOD = 3σ/K, the limit of detection is calculated to be 3.5 nM. In addition, the detection performance of CDs-ABT for BRH was compared with other reported methods, our method has combined advantages (Table 1
                        ). After adding 100 μM BRH to the mother liquor of CDs, the fluorescence intensity of CDs only changed slightly, so the direct use of CDs could not detect BRH sensitively (Fig. S5).
